1

00:00:00,000  -->  00:00:03,580
In Python, if a function doesn't explicitly return a value,

2

00:00:03,580  -->  00:00:05,720
it automatically returns none.

3

00:00:05,720  -->  00:00:07,560
This is Python's way of saying,

4

00:00:07,560  -->  00:00:11,040
I have no output for you and is especially useful

5

00:00:11,040  -->  00:00:15,080
when a function is meant to perform an action without needing to give anything back.

6

00:00:15,080  -->  00:00:18,500
If you remember from our generator example was baking cookies,

7

00:00:18,500  -->  00:00:23,255
we actually used none to create a default value of nothing for a parameter.

8

00:00:23,255  -->  00:00:27,870
If we use this function and don't pass in a second parameter for baked cookies,

9

00:00:27,870  -->  00:00:29,590
